35 template <class T, class Alloc, typename... Args>
36 T* create_impl(const Alloc& allocator, Args&& ... args)
37 {
38  typename std::allocator_traits<Alloc>:: template rebind_alloc<T> alloc(allocator);
39  T* storage = alloc.allocate(1);
40  try
41  {
42  std::allocator_traits<Alloc>:: template rebind_traits<T>::construct(alloc, storage, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
43  }
44  catch (...)
45  {
46  alloc.deallocate(storage,1);
47  throw;
48  }
49  return storage;
50 }
51 
52 template <class T, class Alloc>
53 void destroy_impl(const Alloc& allocator, T* p)
54 {
55  typename std::allocator_traits<Alloc>:: template rebind_alloc<T> alloc(allocator);
56  std::allocator_traits<Alloc>:: template rebind_traits<T>::destroy(alloc, p);
57  alloc.deallocate(p,1);
58 }

302  struct string_dataA
303  {
304  string_data data;
305  char_type c[1];
306  };
307  typedef typename std::aligned_storage<sizeof(string_dataA), JSONCONS_ALIGNOF(string_dataA)>::type storage_type;
308 
309  static size_t aligned_size(size_t n)
310  {
311  return sizeof(storage_type) + n;
312  }
313 
314  string_data* create_string_data(const char_type* s, size_t length, const string_allocator& allocator)
315  {
316  size_t mem_size = aligned_size(length*sizeof(char_type));
317 
318  typename std::allocator_traits<string_allocator>:: template rebind_alloc<char> alloc(allocator);
319 
320  char* storage = alloc.allocate(mem_size);
321  string_data* ps = new(storage)string_data(allocator);
322  auto psa = reinterpret_cast<string_dataA*>(storage);
323 
324  ps->p_ = new(&psa->c)char_type[length + 1];
325  memcpy(ps->p_, s, length*sizeof(char_type));
326  ps->p_[length] = 0;
327  ps->length_ = length;
328  return ps;
329  }
330 
331  void destroy_string_data(const string_allocator& allocator, string_data* p)
332  {
333  size_t mem_size = aligned_size(p->length_*sizeof(char_type));
334  typename std::allocator_traits<string_allocator>:: template rebind_alloc<char> alloc(allocator);
335  alloc.deallocate(reinterpret_cast<char*>(p),mem_size);
336  }

522  void init_variant(const variant& var)
523  {
524  type_ = var.type_;
525  switch (type_)
526  {
527  case value_types::null_t:
528  case value_types::empty_object_t:
529  break;
530  case value_types::double_t:
531  length_or_precision_ = 0;
532  value_.double_val_ = var.value_.double_val_;
533  break;
534  case value_types::integer_t:
535  value_.integer_val_ = var.value_.integer_val_;
536  break;
537  case value_types::uinteger_t:
538  value_.uinteger_val_ = var.value_.uinteger_val_;
539  break;
540  case value_types::bool_t:
541  value_.bool_val_ = var.value_.bool_val_;
542  break;
543  case value_types::small_string_t:
544  length_or_precision_ = var.length_or_precision_;
545  std::memcpy(value_.small_string_val_,var.value_.small_string_val_,var.length_or_precision_*sizeof(char_type));
546  value_.small_string_val_[length_or_precision_] = 0;
547  break;
548  case value_types::string_t:
549  //value_.string_val_ = create_impl<string_type>(var.value_.string_val_->get_allocator(), *(var.value_.string_val_), string_allocator(var.value_.string_val_->get_allocator()));
550  value_.string_val_ = create_string_data(var.value_.string_val_->data(), var.value_.string_val_->length(), string_allocator(var.value_.string_val_->get_allocator()));
551  break;
552  case value_types::array_t:
553  value_.array_val_ = create_impl<array>(var.value_.array_val_->get_allocator(), *(var.value_.array_val_), array_allocator(var.value_.array_val_->get_allocator()));
554  break;
555  case value_types::object_t:
556  value_.object_val_ = create_impl<object>(var.value_.object_val_->get_allocator(), *(var.value_.object_val_), object_allocator(var.value_.object_val_->get_allocator()));
557  break;
558  case value_types::any_t:
559  value_.any_val_ = create_impl<any>(var.value_.any_val_->get_allocator(), *(var.value_.any_val_));
560  break;
561  default:
562  break;
563  }
564  }

571  void destroy_variant()

573  switch (type_)

577  destroy_string_data(value_.string_val_->get_allocator(), value_.string_val_);
578  break;
579  case value_types::array_t:
580  destroy_impl(value_.array_val_->get_allocator(), value_.array_val_);
581  break;
582  case value_types::object_t:
583  destroy_impl(value_.object_val_->get_allocator(), value_.object_val_);
584  break;
585  case value_types::any_t:
586  destroy_impl(value_.any_val_->get_allocator(), value_.any_val_);
587  break;
588  default:
589  break;
590  }

593  variant& operator=(const variant& val)

712  value_.integer_val_ = val;
713  }
714 
715  void assign(uint64_t val)
716  {
717  destroy_variant();
718  type_ = value_types::uinteger_t;
719  value_.uinteger_val_ = val;
720  }
721 
722  void assign(double val, uint8_t precision = 0)
723  {
724  destroy_variant();
725  type_ = value_types::double_t;

727  value_.double_val_ = val;
728  }

733  type_ = value_types::bool_t;

742 
743  void assign(const any& rhs)
744  {
745  destroy_variant();

748  }
749 
750  bool operator!=(const variant& rhs) const
751  {
752  return !(*this == rhs);
753  }
754 
755  bool operator==(const variant& rhs) const
756  {
757  if (is_number() & rhs.is_number())
758  {
759  switch (type_)
760  {
761  case value_types::integer_t:
762  switch (rhs.type_)
763  {
764  case value_types::integer_t:
765  return value_.integer_val_ == rhs.value_.integer_val_;
766  case value_types::uinteger_t:
767  return value_.integer_val_ == rhs.value_.uinteger_val_;
768  case value_types::double_t:
769  return value_.integer_val_ == rhs.value_.double_val_;
770  default:
771  break;
772  }
773  break;
774  case value_types::uinteger_t:
775  switch (rhs.type_)
776  {
777  case value_types::integer_t:
778  return value_.uinteger_val_ == rhs.value_.integer_val_;
779  case value_types::uinteger_t:
780  return value_.uinteger_val_ == rhs.value_.uinteger_val_;
781  case value_types::double_t:
782  return value_.uinteger_val_ == rhs.value_.double_val_;
783  default:
784  break;
785  }
786  break;
787  case value_types::double_t:
788  switch (rhs.type_)
789  {
790  case value_types::integer_t:
791  return value_.double_val_ == rhs.value_.integer_val_;
792  case value_types::uinteger_t:
793  return value_.double_val_ == rhs.value_.uinteger_val_;
794  case value_types::double_t:
795  return value_.double_val_ == rhs.value_.double_val_;
796  default:
797  break;
798  }
799  break;
800  default:
801  break;
802  }
803  }
804 
805  switch (type_)
806  {
807  case value_types::bool_t:
808  return type_ == rhs.type_ && value_.bool_val_ == rhs.value_.bool_val_;
809  case value_types::null_t:
810  return type_ == rhs.type_;
811  case value_types::empty_object_t:
812  return type_ == rhs.type_ || (rhs.type_ == value_types::object_t && rhs.empty());
813  case value_types::small_string_t:
814  return type_ == rhs.type_ && length_or_precision_ == rhs.length_or_precision_ ? std::char_traits<char_type>::compare(value_.small_string_val_,rhs.value_.small_string_val_,length_or_precision_) == 0 : false;
815  case value_types::string_t:
816  return type_ == rhs.type_ && *(value_.string_val_) == *(rhs.value_.string_val_);
817  case value_types::array_t:
818  return type_ == rhs.type_ && *(value_.array_val_) == *(rhs.value_.array_val_);
819  break;
820  case value_types::object_t:
821  return (type_ == rhs.type_ && *(value_.object_val_) == *(rhs.value_.object_val_)) || (rhs.type_ == value_types::empty_object_t && empty());
822  break;
823  case value_types::any_t:
824  return type_ == rhs.type_;
825  default:
826  // throw
827  break;
828  }
829  return false;
830  }
831 
832  bool is_null() const JSONCONS_NOEXCEPT
833  {
834  return type_ == value_types::null_t;
835  }
836 
837  bool is_bool() const JSONCONS_NOEXCEPT
838  {
839  return type_ == value_types::bool_t;
840  }
841 
842  bool empty() const JSONCONS_NOEXCEPT
843  {
844  switch (type_)
845  {
846  case value_types::small_string_t:
847  return length_or_precision_ == 0;
848  case value_types::string_t:
849  return value_.string_val_->length() == 0;
850  case value_types::array_t:
851  return value_.array_val_->size() == 0;
852  case value_types::empty_object_t:
853  return true;
854  case value_types::object_t:
855  return value_.object_val_->size() == 0;
856  default:
857  return false;
858  }
859  }
860 
861  bool is_string() const JSONCONS_NOEXCEPT
862  {
863  return (type_ == value_types::string_t) | (type_ == value_types::small_string_t);
864  }
865 
866  bool is_number() const JSONCONS_NOEXCEPT
867  {
868  return type_ == value_types::double_t || type_ == value_types::integer_t || type_ == value_types::uinteger_t;
869  }
870 
871  void swap(variant& rhs)
872  {
873  using std::swap;
874  if (this == &rhs)
875  {
876  // same object, do nothing
877  }
878  else
879  {
880  swap(type_, rhs.type_);
881  swap(length_or_precision_, rhs.length_or_precision_);
882  swap(value_, rhs.value_);
883  }
884  }
885 
886  value_types type_;
887  uint8_t length_or_precision_;
888  union
889  {
890  double double_val_;
891  int64_t integer_val_;
892  uint64_t uinteger_val_;
893  bool bool_val_;
894  object* object_val_;
895  array* array_val_;
896  any* any_val_;
897  string_data* string_val_;
898  char_type small_string_val_[sizeof(int64_t)/sizeof(char_type)];
899  } value_;
900  };

1816  void to_stream(basic_json_output_handler<char_type>& handler) const
1817  {
1818  switch (var_.type_)
1819  {
1820  case value_types::small_string_t:
1821  handler.value(var_.value_.small_string_val_,var_.length_or_precision_);
1822  break;
1823  case value_types::string_t:
1824  handler.value(var_.value_.string_val_->data(),var_.value_.string_val_->length());
1825  break;
1826  case value_types::double_t:
1827  handler.value(var_.value_.double_val_, var_.length_or_precision_);
1828  break;
1829  case value_types::integer_t:
1830  handler.value(var_.value_.integer_val_);
1831  break;
1832  case value_types::uinteger_t:
1833  handler.value(var_.value_.uinteger_val_);
1834  break;
1835  case value_types::bool_t:
1836  handler.value(var_.value_.bool_val_);
1837  break;
1838  case value_types::null_t:
1839  handler.value(null_type());
1840  break;
1841  case value_types::empty_object_t:
1842  handler.begin_object();
1843  handler.end_object();
1844  break;
1845  case value_types::object_t:
1846  {
1847  handler.begin_object();
1848  object* o = var_.value_.object_val_;
1849  for (const_object_iterator it = o->begin(); it != o->end(); ++it)
1850  {
1851  handler.name((it->name()).data(),it->name().length());
1852  it->value().to_stream(handler);
1853  }
1854  handler.end_object();
1855  }
1856  break;
1857  case value_types::array_t:
1858  {
1859  handler.begin_array();
1860  array *o = var_.value_.array_val_;
1861  for (const_array_iterator it = o->begin(); it != o->end(); ++it)
1862  {
1863  it->to_stream(handler);
1864  }
1865  handler.end_array();
1866  }
1867  break;
1868  case value_types::any_t:
1869  var_.value_.any_val_->to_stream(handler);
1870  break;
1871  default:
1872  break;
1873  }
1874  }

1899  size_t count(const string_type& name) const
1900  {
